ruggling to grow up amidst his perplexing asthma, his eccentric Catholic parents, and his mystifying quasi-erections. All of the stories are grounded in the allure of language, the luxuriance of detail, and the celebration of human compulsion and obsession.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311071692440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814741498.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814741498zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814741498/original  a978-3-11-071692-4 New York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA